8057.description: The Ice Queen's pets' favorite food.

8058.description: Dr. Chaos's research report. It's locked.

8059.description: Unlock the padlock to read Dr. Chaos's research report.

8062.name: Blood of Maille Lizardman
8062.description: Blood obtained by killing Maille Lizardmen.

8063.name: Leg of King Araneid
8063.description: The legs obtained by defeating King Araneid.

8064.name: Visitor's Mark
8064.description: Permits entry to the Pagan Temple. Don't lose it!

8065.name: Faded Visitor's Mark
8065.description: This faded mark permits entry to the Pagan Temple.

8066.name: Necromancer's Heart
8066.description: Obtain this necromantic heart by slaying Bone Animators, Bone Slayers or Skull Animators.

8067.name: Pagan's Mark
8067.description: Permits entry and access to the chapel of the Pagan Temple.

8068.name: Pagan Totem
8068.description: The totem obtained by defeating the Pagans.

8069.name: Monk's Scripture
8069.description: The scripture obtained by defeating the monks within the Monastery of Silence.

8070.name: Water Bottle
8070.description: The bottle from Greymore. Pour the water into the Holy Grail in the Splendor Room and take it with you.

8071.name: Bottle of water from the Holy Grail
8071.description: The bottle containing the water from the Holy Grail in the Splendor Room. Take it to Greymore.

8072.name: Antelope Skin
8072.description: The exceptional hide needed to create the magical scroll.

8073.name: Frintezza's Magic Force Field Removal Scroll
8073.description: The scroll that permits passage though Frintezza's Magic Force Field. Meet his guide near the Imperial Tomb entrance and he will let you enter the forbidden area.

8074.name: Watching Eyes
8074.description: This "Wandering Eye" has been harassing the farmers of Floran. Take it to Almankel in Floran Village.

8075.name: Roughly Hewn Rock Golem Shard
8075.description: This is a fragment from a Roughly Hewn Rock Golem. Take it to Almankel in Floran Village.

8076.name: Delu Lizardman's Scale
8076.description: This is a scale of the Delu Lizardman that has been harassing the farmers of Floran. Take it to Almankel in Floran Village.

8077.name: Silver Ice Crystal
8077.description: A crystal obtained from a monster. When processed, it becomes the Black Ice Crystal.

8078.name: Black Ice Crystal
8078.description: When stuck into a target, the character becomes violent.

8079.name: Misa's Letter
8079.description: A secret letter from Misa to Rafforty. Don't break the seal!

8080.name: Rafforty's Letter
8080.description: A secret letter from Rafforty to Misa.

8082.name: Report Piece
8082.description: A fragment of the report from the stone statue.

8083.name: Scout's Memo
8083.description: A scribbled note written by a scout searching the nest.

8084.name: Crystal of Purity
8084.description: This white crystal was expelled by a wild beast whose heart was pure.

8086.name: Box Containing the Fire of Holy Spirit
8086.description: Box containing the Fire of the Holy Spirit

8087.name: Cursed Doll
8087.description: An enchanted doll that has been said to control the evil creatures of the Ragna Orcs.

8089.name: Cursed Grave Goods
8089.description: Items made by angry spirits to use physical force.

8090.name: Electric Wave Detector
8090.description: This rod lights up in the presence of strong electric waves. It is presently unlit.

8091.name: Electric Wave Detector
8091.description: This rod lights up in the presence of strong electric waves. It is presently lit.

8092.name: Telescope Golem's Corpse
8092.description: Metal obtained from hunting the Scout Golem. It may be concealing something.

8093.name: Golem's Dispatcher
8093.description: Dispatcher obtained from hunting the Telescope Golem.

8094.name: Storage Medium
8094.description: The storage medium taken from the Golem. It is empty.

8095.name: Storage Medium
8095.description: The storage medium taken from the Golem. It contains information.

8096.name: Ginzu Golem's Black Box
8096.description: The analysis device obtained from the Ginzu Golem.

8097.name: X-688
8097.description: A curious scroll found on Dr. Chaos's bookshelf.

8098.name: Supplying Goods for Railroad Worker
8098.description: Supplies sent by a Dwarven Elder to a Railroad Worker.

8099.name: Thief Guild's Mark
8099.description: An animal's tooth worn by the thieves of the Plunderous Plains.
